    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>STRIKE DISRUPTS 2 INDIA INDUSTRIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Hari Kumar</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kumar, Hari</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>India's banking and insurance industries are paralyzed by one-day strike called to protest government's programs for economic reforms, which coalition of organizations calls 'anti-poor people' (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>India's banking and insurance industries were largely paralyzed by a one-day strike called to protest the government's programs for economic reforms, which a coalition of organizations called ''anti-poor people.'' The National Platform of Mass Organizations, an umbrella group of trade unionists, farmers and students, said 20 million people participated.</p>
        <p>Hari Kumar (NYT)</p>
      </block>
